title: Sylvia's Lovers
creator: Elizabeth Gaskell
description: LibriVox recording of Sylvia's Lovers, by Elizabeth Gaskell. The novel begins in the 1790s in the coastal town of Monkshaven. Sylvia Robson lives with her parents on a farm, and is loved by her rather dull Quaker cousin Philip. She, however, meets and falls in love with Charlie Kinraid, a sailor on a whaling vessel, and they become engaged, although few people know of the engagement. But Charlie gets press-ganged and have to leave without a word...
